Package me.masstrix.eternalnature.config

Class Configuration

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.masstrix.eternalnature.config.Configuration
  • public class Configuration
extends java.lang.Object
    Handles the reloading of a config file. When ever the reload method is called then it will update all subscribed Configurable.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Configuration

        public Configuration​(org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin plugin,
                     java.lang.String name)
        Creates a new configuration. This works from the plugins data folder.
        Parameters:
        plugin - plugin the configuration is being created from.
        name - name of the config. This can include a path (eg. data/config) and the .yml extension at the end is optional as it will be added it it is not already. Both config and config.yml will read the same file.

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe​(Configurable configurable)
        Subscribes a configurable to the handler. When subscribed the configurable will have Configurable.updateConfig(ConfigurationSection) called when ever the reload() method is called for this handler.
        Parameters:
        configurable - configurable to subscribe to the handler.
